title: AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'keys'
body:
**Operating system and DeepLabCut version**
MacOS Mojave 10.14.3, with an Anaconda Env, & DeepLabCut 2.0.

**Describe the problem**
When I run the command to extract my frames "deeplabcut.extract_frames(path_config, 'automatic', 'kmeans')", it causes this problem:

AttributeError                            Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-3-caf2905c8f6f> in <module>()
----> 1 deeplabcut.extract_frames(path_config, 'automatic', 'kmeans')

/Users/leonardkarsunky/Documents/Bachelor Project 2019/DeepLabCut/deeplabcut/generate_training_dataset/frame_extraction.py in extract_frames(config, mode, algo, crop, userfeedback, cluster_step, cluster_resizewidth, cluster_color, opencv)
    111             raise Exception("Perhaps consider extracting more, or a natural number of frames.")
    112 
--> 113         videos = cfg['video_sets'].keys()
    114         if opencv:
    115             import cv2

AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'keys'

**How to Reproduce the problem**
The only steps I did were:
1. import deeplabcut
2. deeplabcut.create_new_project('WhiskerTracking_SC016c_2', 'karsunky', ['leonardkarsunky/Documents/Bachelor\ Project\ 2019/SC016c_2'])
3. path_config = '/Users/leonardkarsunky/Documents/Bachelor Project 2019/DeepLabCut/WhiskerTracking_SC016c_2-karsunky-2019-03-12/config.yaml'
4. deeplabcut.extract_frames(path_config, 'automatic', 'kmeans')

If anyone can help it would be greatly appreciated!
